description: Up for sale is a 1967 Aquasport 22-2 Flatback.  Completely restored and documented in 2007/2008 from the stringers up with all composite materials by Bateau2.  The entire restoration can be seen here :  https://boatbuildercentral.wordpress.com/2015/10/29/an-in-depth-rebuild-of-a-classic-aquasport-22-flatback/ During the restoration the stringers were replaced with solid core material, the transom was enclosed and a porta bracket was added.  It was rigged with a 2007 Mercury 150 Optimax which currently has 360 hours and was recently serviced with a new oil pump installed and given a clean bill of health.  I cruise at 4000 rpm at 30mph.  The boat was just repainted Seafoam Green in December 2015.  Also new within the last 6 months is the trolling motor (motor guide XI5), the Simrad GO7 chart plotter/fishfinder with navionics .  I recently re-plumbed the live well adding a 1600 gph pump and new 1 1/8 flex hose.  The front casting platform has three hatches, the middle hatch has a cast net bucket inside to keep your net out of the way while fishing.  There is so much more to this boat but talking about it does not do it justice.  A lot of money has gone into this classic boat and to restore one like this would cost a lot more than the asking price.  I am including the aluminum trailer which is perfectly fit for the boat and pulls great.  Please feel free to email or text any questions, phone calls are difficult to answer during the day but text and email I can reply quickly.  If necessary I can call you in the evenings.  The boat is titled and I do have the clean title in hand. Update: I have been flooded with questions on the boat so I decided to list out some of the other items on the boat. Engine: 2007 Mercury Optimax (2 stroke) 150hp. Hours: 360 Hydraulic steering Morse controls Porta Bracket adjustable height lift. Comes with a 3 blade aluminum prop and a 4 blade SS prop. Dual 8ft. power poles Hydraulic trim tabs, needs new relays. . .boat really does not need tabs but I left them on without installing new relays. Ping pong style scullpers. The hull was professionally painted 01/16 sea foam green. Motor Guide Xi5, bought in 03/2016.  24v system. 2 dedicated batteries for the trolling motor attached to a battery tender trickle charger. New Simrad Go7 chartplotter, sonar, downscan w/ navionics +. New Kenwood head unit, JVC amp, 12 inch sub, and 2 new Pioneer speakers. New Rule 1600 GPH live well pump and new 1 1/2" inlet line. 2 bank on board battery charger 2 batteries under the console for motor and house on a battery selector. Freshwater wash down pump and tank w/ hose under console. Marine radio under console LED front and rear deck lights 6 rod holders along the railing, 4 rod holders in seat/livewell 2 Seat post pads installed in front deck, included is a small wedge seat and an umbrella which was made to fit through the posts. The boat has 2 bilge pumps front and rear, both operate correctly. Large Bimini top Trailer: Dual axle Fastload aluminum rail trailer. 4 bunks custom fit for the boat. New front rollers, new strap, new chain, new guide posts and new lights. Ok, I think thats about it. . .hopefully this answers some questions, if not please feel free to contact me.
title: 1967 Aquasport 22-2 Flatback

Product Description Product Description Whether you're maneuvering rapids or meandering down a stream, the Coleman Colossus Inflatable Boat is ready, durable and certified by the National Marine Manufacturers Association. The Colossus Two-Person Boat is constructed with three separate air chambers, each of which is sealed with Coleman's unique Double Lock valve technology. Multiple chambers make the boat more secure and resistant to punctures. The Colossus Two-Person Inflatable Boat comes with two oars and features dual oar locks and a rope grab line. Guaranteed not to leak, thanks to Coleman's exclusive Airtight System, the Colossus' heavy-duty, puncture-resistant PVC and patented Double-Lock valve prevent accidental air loss. Amazon.com Suitable for maneuvering rapids, meandering down a stream, crossing a lake, or taking passengers ashore from a yacht, this 82-inch x 40-inch inflatable boat accommodates two. It consists of three separate air chambers, each sealed with a double-lock leak-free valve for safety. The airtight system is guaranteed not to leak. (Pump not included; sold separately.) The boat is made of heavy-duty, puncture-resistant 15-gauge PVC. The boat supports up to 435 pounds. Other features include two oars, two oar locks, and a rope grab-line for docking or hauling the boat onto shore. The 45-inch plastic oars feature contoured, shovel-shaped blades that make it easy to propel the boat quickly. The oars are ribbed for durability and are easy to assemble and disassemble for storage and portability. Specifications: Capacity: 2 people, 435 lbs Length: 82" Width: 40" Material: heavy-duty, puncture-resistant 15-gauge PVC 3 separate air chambers, each with double-lock leak-free valve
title: Coleman 2-Person Colossus Inflatable Boat
